    "body": "> This component isn't created as part of our quo2 library, but we must align with the design team to check if we will reuse it and ask for complete specifications about it.\r\n\r\n@ulisesmac will also be used in the composer. So, we need to build it as a global (bottom) sheet.\r\n\r\nThe Status Desktop app uses the Unicode v14 emoji set. We can use the same set on mobile, and create this emoji picker. We can't use external libraries as they are difficult to style and won't match our design.\r\n\r\nI can pick up this issue üëç \r\n\r\nOn the same note, as you can see from the screenshot attached to the issue, the emojis are using [Twemoji](https://twemoji.twitter.com/). I'm researching Twemoji integration on mobile https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/17072. There are a few pitfalls to the emoji library which I'm exploring. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
